Key Performance Metrics
To prove your system works, you must go beyond simple "Accuracy." In cybersecurity, a False Negative (missing an actual attack) is much more dangerous than a False Positive (a false alarm).
Accuracy: Overall percentage of correct predictions (Normal vs. Attack).
Precision: Out of all traffic flagged as an attack, how much was actually an attack? (Reduces False Alarms).
Recall (Detection Rate): Out of all actual attacks, how many did the AI catch? (Critical for security).
F1-Score: The harmonic mean of Precision and Recall; the most balanced metric for NIDS.
Inference Latency: The time taken to analyze a single packet (usually measured in milliseconds). For real-time use, this should be < 1.0 ms.
