Visualizing the Findings
To make your project professional, include the following visualizations:
A. Confusion Matrix
A heatmap that shows exactly where the model gets confused.
True Positives (TP): Correctly identified attacks.
False Positives (FP): Normal traffic wrongly flagged (Annoying for users).
False Negatives (FN): Attacks missed by the system (The biggest failure).
B. ROC Curve (Receiver Operating Characteristic)
A graph showing the trade-off between the "Detection Rate" and "False Alarm Rate." A curve that hugs the top-left corner indicates a superior model.
Attack Category Detection Rate Typical Feature Indicator
DoS / DDoS 99.8% High packet count, short duration.
Probe (Scanning) 96.5% Multiple destination ports from one source.
R2L (Unauthorized Login) 84.2% Failed login attempts, specific protocol flags.
Zero-Day (New) 78.0% High deviation from baseline "Normal" behavior.
